obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28606)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28606&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Andhra State Act, 1953.`
  line
  line `(2) This Part and sections 43, 54, 58, 61, 62, 63, 64, 66 and 69 shall come into force at once, and`
  line `all other provisions of this Act shall come into force on the 1st day of October, 1953.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28607)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28607&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 1st day of October, 1953;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(c) "Assembly constituency", "Council constituency" and "Parliamentary constituency" have`
  line `the same meaning as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950; (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(d) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of the State of`
  line `Madras or Mysore as constituted immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(e) "Order" means an Order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "sitting member" in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who immediately before the appointed day is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(g) "transferred territory" means the territory added to the State of Mysore by`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28608)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of Andhra State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28608&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, there shall be formed a Part A`
  line `State to be known as the State of Andhra comprising the territories which immediately before that day`
  line `were comprised in Srikakulam, Visakhapatnam, East Godavari, West Godavari, Krishna, Guntur,`
  line `Nellore, Kurnool, Anantapur, Cuddapah and Chittoor districts and Alur, Adoni and Rayadrugtaluks of`
  line `Bellary district in the State of Madras and the said territories shall thereupon cease to form part of the`
  line `State of Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the power of the State Government to alter hereafter the extent,`
  line `boundaries and names of districts, the said taluks of Alur and Adoni shall be included in, and become`
  line `part of, Kurnool district, and the said taluk of Rayadrug shall be included in, and become part of,`
  line `Anantapur district.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28609)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Transfer of territory from Madras to Mysore.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28609&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, there shall`
  line `be added to the State of Mysore the territory which immediately before that day was comprised in the`
  line `taluks of Bellary district other than Alur, Adoni and Rayadrug in the State of Madras, and the said`
  line `territory shall thereupon cease to form part of the State of Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the power of the State Government to alter hereafter the extent,`
  line `boundaries and names of districts, the transferred territory shall form a separate district to be known`
  line `as Bellary district.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28610)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28610&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `In the First Schedule to the`
  line Constitution.—
  line
  line `(a) in Part A, Entries 1 to 9 shall be renumbered as Entries 2 to 10 respectively, and before`
  line `Entry 2 as so renumbered, the entry "1. Andhra" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) in Part A, in the description of the territories of States—`
  line
  line `(i) before the paragraph relating to the territory of the State of Assam, the following`
  line `paragraph shall be inserted namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territory of the State of Andhra shall comprise the territories specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Andhra State Act, 1953"; and`
  line
  line `(ii) at the end of the last paragraph, the following shall be added, namely:—`
  line
  line `"but in the case of the State of Madras shall not include the territories specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 and sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Andhra State Act, 1953";`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) in Part B, at the end of the paragraph containing the description of the Territories of States,`
  line `the following shall be added, namely:—`
  line
  line `"and in the case of the State of Mysore shall also comprise the territory specified in subsection`
  line `(1) of section 4 of the Andhra State Act, 1953."`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28611)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Representation in the Council of States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28611&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The number of seats allotted to the State of Madras`
  line `in the Council of States shall be reduced from 27 to 18, and there shall be allotted 12 seats to the State`
  line `of Andhra in the said Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28612)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amendment of the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28612&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `In the Fourth Schedule to the`
  line Constitution—
  line
  line `(a) in the Table of Seats relating to the States specified in Part A of the First Schedule—`
  line
  line `(i) entries 1 to 9 shall be renumbered as entries 2 to 10 respectively;`
  line
  line `(ii) before entry 2 as so renumbered, the entry "1. Andhra...12" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(iii) in column 2, for the figures "27" and "145" the figures "18" and "148" shall`
  line `respectively be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) at the end of the Table of Seats, for the figures "204" the figures "207" shall be`
  line substituted.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28613)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28613&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The nine sitting members of the Council of States`
  line `representing the State of Madras whose names are specified in Part I of the First Schedule shall be`
  line `deemed to have been elected by the elected Members of the Legislative Assembly of Andhra to fill`
  line `nine of the seats allotted to the State of Andhra in the Council of States; and the remaining eighteen`
  line `sitting members whose names are specified in Part II of that Schedule shall continue to be members of`
  line `the Council of States representing the State of Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28614)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bye-election to fill vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28614&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the appointed day, there shall be held`
  line `a bye-election to fill the vacancies existing on the appointed day in the seats allotted to the State of`
  line `Andhra in the Council of States.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28615)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28615&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided in sub-section (2), the terms of office of the`
  line `members specified in the First Schedule shall remain unaltered, that is to say, as indicated in that`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(2) The term of office—`
  line
  line `(a) of one of the two members specified against serial numbers 4 and 5 in Part I of the First`
  line `Schedule shall be increased so as to expire on the 2nd day of April, 1958, and`
  line
  line `(b) of one of the seven members specified against serial numbers 7 to 13 in Part II of that`
  line `Schedule shall be reduced so as to expire on the 2nd April, 1954.`
  line
  line `(3) The member whose term of office is to be increased under clause (a) of sub-section (2) and the`
  line `member whose term of office is to be reduced under clause (b) of that sub-section shall be determined`
  line `as soon as may be after the appointed day by lot drawn in such manner as the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of each of the three members to be elected by the elected members of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Andhra under section 9 shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28616)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Representation in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28616&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The number of seats allotted in the House`
  line `of the People to the State of Madras shall be reduced from 75 to 46, the number of seats allotted to the`
  line `State of Mysore shall be increased from 11 to 12, and there shall be allotted 28 seats to the State of`
  line `Andhra in that House.`
  line
  line `(2) In the First Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950)—`
  line
  line `(a) In the Part relating to Part A States,—`
  line
  line `(i) entries 1 to 9 shall be renumbered as entries 2 to 10 respectively, and before entry 2 as`
  line `so renumbered, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"1. Andhra....28"; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the entry in column 2 against Madras, the entry "46" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the part relating to Part B States, for the entry in column 2 against Mysore, the entry`
  line `"12" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28617)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28617&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies (Madras) Order, 1951 and the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies (Mysore) Order, 1951 shall, until other provision is made by law, have effect subject`
  line `to the modifications directed by the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28618)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28618&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing a constituency which on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 12`
  line `stands transferred, whether with or without alteration of boundaries, to the State of Andhra or to the`
  line `State of Mysore, shall be deemed to have been elected to the House of the People by that constituency`
  line `as so transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28619)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Electoral rolls for modified Parliamentary constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28619&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of section 12, the extent of a Parliamentary constituency has altered, the electoral roll for that constituency as so altered shall as from the appointed day and until it is revised in accordance`
  line `with law, be deemed to consist of so much of the electoral roll or rolls for any Parliamentary`
  line `constituency or constituencies as relate to the areas comprised within the constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28620)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Strength of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28620&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total number of seats to be filled by persons`
  line `chosen by direct election—`
  line
  line `(a) in the Legislative Assembly of Andhra, shall be 140,`
  line
  line `(b) in the Legislative Assembly of Madras, shall be reduced from 375 to 230, and`
  line
  line `(c) in the Legislative Assembly of Mysore, shall be increased from 99 to 104.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950)—`
  line
  line `(a) in the Part relating to Part A States,—`
  line
  line `(i) entries 1 to 9 shall be renumbered as entries 2 to 10 respectively and before entry 2 as`
  line `so renumbered, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"1. Andhra.....140"; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the entry in column 2 against Madras, the entry "230" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the Part relating to Part B States, for the entry in column 2 against Mysore the entry`
  line `"104" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28621)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Allocation of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28621&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of Madras`
  line `representing a constituency which on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 12`
  line `stands transferred, whether with or without alteration of boundaries, to the State of Andhra or to the`
  line `State of Mysore shall, as from the appointed day, cease to be a member of the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of Madras and shall be deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Andhra or, as the`
  line `case may be, of Mysore by that constituency as so transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of Madras nominated to that Assembly under`
  line `article 333 to represent the Anglo-Indian community shall, notwithstanding the diminution in the area`
  line `of that State continue to represent the said community in that Assembly under that Article.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28622)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Duration of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28622&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The period of five years referred to in clause (1) of`
  line `article 172 shall, in the case of the Legislative Assembly of Andhra, be deemed to have commenced`
  line `on the date on which it actually commenced in the case of the Legislative Assembly of Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) The changes in the composition of the Legislative Assemblies of Madras and Mysore shall not`
  line `affect the duration of either of those Assemblies as provided under clause (1) of article 172.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28623)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Electoral rolls for modified Assembly constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28623&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where by virtue of the provisions`
  line `of section 12 the extent of an Assembly constituency has altered, the electoral roll for that`
  line `constituency as so altered shall, as from the appointed day and until it is revised in accordance with`
  line `law, be deemed to consist of so much of the electoral roll or rolls for any Assembly constituency or`
  line `constituencies as relate to the areas comprised within the constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28624)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Madras Legislative Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28624&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the Legislative Council of Madras there shall be 51`
  line `seats of which—`
  line
  line `(a) the numbers to be filled by persons elected by the electorates referred to in sub-clauses`
  line `(a), (b) and (c) of clause (3) of article 171 shall be 14, 4 and 4 respectively;`
  line
  line `(b) the number to be filled by persons elected by the members of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Madras in accordance with the provisions of sub-clause (d) of the said clause shall be 18; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number to be filled by the persons nominated by the Governor of Madras in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-clause (e) of the said clause shall be 11:`
  line
  line `Provided that as from the 21st day of April, 1954—`
  line
  line `(a) the number of seats to be filled by persons elected by the electorates referred to in subclause`
  line `(b) of clause (3) of article 171 shall be increased to 6, and`
  line
  line `(b) the number of seats to be filled by persons referred to in clause (c) of this sub-section shall`
  line `be reduced to 9.`
  line
  line `(2) The two additional seats allotted under clause (a) of the proviso to sub-section (1) shall, for`
  line `the purpose of filling them for the first time, be deemed to be seats rendered vacant by the members of`
  line `the Legislative Council of Madras retiring on the expiration of their terms of office on the 20th day of`
  line `April, 1954.`
  line
  line `(3) The Third Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) as from the appointed day and until the 21st day of April, 1954, stand amended as`
  line `follows:—`
  line
  line `For the entry relating to Madras, the entry—`
  line
  line `"3. Madras 51 14 4 4 18 11" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) as from the 21st day of April, 1954, stand amended at follows:—`
  line
  line `For the entry relating to Madras, the entry—`
  line
  line `"3. Madras 51 14 6 4 18 9" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28625)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Madras Council Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28625&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Madras)`
  line `Order, 1951, shall, until other provision is made by law have effect subject to the modifications`
  line `directed by the Third Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that as from the 21st day of April, 1954, the Table appended to paragraph 2 of that Order`
  line `shall have effect subject to the further modification that for the entry in column 3 thereof against`
  line `"Madras (Graduates)" constituency the entry "6" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28626)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Members of the Madras Legislative Council and their terms of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28626&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sitting`
  line `members of the Legislative Council of Madras whose names are not specified in the Fourth Schedule`
  line `shall, on the appointed day, cease to be members of that Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting members of the Legislative Council representing the Madras South (Graduates)`
  line `constituency and the Madras South (Teachers) constituency shall, as from the appointed day, be`
  line `deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Council of Madras by the Madras (Graduates)`
  line `constituency and the Madras (Teachers) constituency, respectively.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms of office of those sitting members who do not cease to be members of the`
  line `Legislative Council on the appointed day shall be determined in accordance with the provisions`
  line `contained in the Fourth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28627)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Mysore Legislative Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28627&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Mysore)`
  line `Order, 1951, shall until other provision is made by law, have effect subject to the modification`
  line `directed by the Fifth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in the said Order to the State of Mysore shall be construed as including the`
  line `territory added to that State by sub-section (1) of section 4.`
  line
  line `(3) The sitting members of the Legislative Council of Mysore representing the Chitaldrug (Local`
  line `Authorities) constituency shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have been elected to that`
  line `Council by the Chitaldrug-cum-Bellary (Local Authorities) constituency.`
  line
  line `(4) Every sitting member of the Legislative Council of Mysore representing the Mysore`
  line `(Graduates) constituency or the Mysore (Teachers) constituency, the boundaries of which are by`
  line `virtue of the provisions of sub-section (2) altered, shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have`
  line `been elected to the said Council by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28628)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Electoral rolls for modified Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28628&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the appointed`
  line `day, the electoral rolls for the Mysore (Graduates) constituency and the Mysore (Teachers)`
  line `constituency shall be revised and an electoral roll shall be prepared for the Chitaldrug-cum-Bellary`
  line `(Local Authorities) constituency for the Mysore Legislative Council in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), and the roll so revised or prepared shall`
  line `come into force immediately upon their final publication in accordance with the rules made under that`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28629)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Revision of the Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28629&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950, and the Constitution (Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950, shall have`
  line `effect subject to the modifications directed by the Sixth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28630)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Rules of Procedure of the Andhra Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28630&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The rules as to procedure and`
  line `conduct of business in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State of Madras shall, until rules are made under clause (1) of article 208, have effect`
  line `in relation to the Legislative Assembly of the Andhra subject to such modifications and adaptations as`
  line `may be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28631)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Amendment of section 2, Act 43 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28631&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Section 2 of the Representation of the People`
  line `Act, 1950, shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) of section 2 and to the said section as so`
  line `renumbered, the following sub-section shall be added, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(2) Any reference in this Act to an order made under section 6, section 9 or section 11 shall,`
  line `unless the context otherwise requires, be construed as including a reference to any such order as`
  line `modified under section 12, section 20 or section 22, as the case may be, of the Andhra State Act,`
  line `1953."`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (28632)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of section 9, Act 81 of 1952.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28632&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In sub-section (3) of section 9 of the`
  line `Delimitation Commission Act, 1952, for the words "and the orders made under either of the said`
  line `Acts" the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"the Andhra State Act, 1953, and the orders made under any of the said Acts."`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (28633)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `High Court for Andhra.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28633&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the 1st day of January, 1956, or such earlier date as`
  line `may be appointed under sub-section (2), there shall be a separate High Court for the State of Andhra`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as "the High Court of Andhra").`
  line
  line `(2) The President may, if a resolution recommending the establishment of a separate High Court`
  line `for the State of Andhra has, after having been adopted by the Legislative Assembly of that State, been`
  line `submitted to him, appoint, by notifications in the Official Gazette, a date earlier than the 1st day of`
  line `January, 1956, for the purpose of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The date mentioned in sub-section (1) or, if an earlier date is appointed under subsection (2),`
  line `the date so appointed is hereinafter referred to as the "prescribed day."`
  line
  line `(4) The principal seat of the High Court of Andhra shall be at such place as the Governor of`
  line `Andhra may, before the prescribed day, by order, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a resolution recommending any place for such principal seat is adopted by the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Andhra, such place shall be appointed by the Governor as the principal Seat.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (28634)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Judges of the Andhra High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28634&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such of the Judges of the High Court at Madras`
  line `holding office immediately before the prescribed day as may be determined by the President shall on`
  line `that day cease to be Judges of the High Court at Madras and become Judges of the High Court of`
  line Andhra.
  line
  line `(2) The persons who by virtue of sub-section (1) become Judges of the High Court of Andhra`
  line `shall, except in the case where any such person is appointed to be the Chief Justice of that High Court,`
  line `rank in that Court according to the priority of their respective appointments as Judges of the High`
  line `Court at Madras.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who by virtue of sub-section (1) becomes a Judge of the High Court of Andhra`
  line `shall, except in the case where a Judge other than the Chief Justice of the High Court at Madras is`
  line `appointed to be the Chief Justice of the High Court of Andhra, continue to be entitled to receive in`
  line `respect of time spent on actual service as a Judge of the High Court of Andhra the special pay which`
  line `he was drawing immediately before the prescribed day under sub-paragraph (2) of paragraph 10 of the`
  line `Second Schedule to the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (28635)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Jurisdiction of Andhra High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28635&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The High Court of Andhra shall have, in respect of`
  line `the territories for the time being included in the State of Andhra, all such original, appellate and other`
  line `jurisdiction as, under the law in force immediately before the prescribed day, is exercisable in respect`
  line `of the said territories or any part thereof by the High Court at Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (28636)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to enrol advocates, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28636&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court of Andhra shall have the like power to`
  line `approve, admit, enroll, remove and suspend advocates and attorneys and to make rules with respect to`
  line `advocates and attorneys, as are, under the law in force immediately before the prescribed day,`
  line `exercisable by the High Court at Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of audience in the High Court of Andhra shall be regulated in accordance with the`
  line `like principles as, immediately before the prescribed day, are in force with respect to the right of`
  line `audience in the High Court at Madras:`
  line
  line `Provided that, subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court of Andhra in the`
  line `exercise of the powers conferred by this section, any person who immediately before the prescribed`
  line `day is an advocate entitled to practice or an attorney entitled to act in the High Court at Madras shall`
  line `be recognised as an advocate or an attorney entitled to practice or to act, as the case may be, in the`
  line `High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (28637)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Practice and procedure in Andhra High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28637&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the`
  line `law in force immediately before the prescribed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High`
  line `Court at Madras shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Andhra and accordingly that High Court shall have all such powers to make rules and orders with respect to`
  line `practice and procedure as are immediately before the prescribed day exercisable by the High Court at`
  line `Madras:`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the prescribed day with`
  line `respect to practice and procedure in the High Court at Madras shall, until varied or revoked by rules or`
  line `orders made by the High Court of Andhra apply with the necessary modifications in relation to`
  line `practice and procedure in the High Court of Andhra as if made by that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (28638)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Custody of the Seal of the Andhra High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28638&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `prescribed day with respect to the custody of the Seal of the High Court at Madras shall, with the`
  line `necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (28639)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28639&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the prescribed`
  line `day with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court at`
  line `Madras shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other`
  line `processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (28640)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28640&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the prescribed day relating to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and Division Courts of the High Court at Madras and with`
  line `respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to the High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (28641)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `The place of sitting of the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28641&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The Judges and Division Courts of the High Court`
  line `of Andhra may sit at such place or places in the State of Andhra other than its principal seat as the`
  line `Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governor of Andhra, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (28642)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Procedure as to appeals to the Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28642&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The law, in force immediately before the`
  line `prescribed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court at Madras and the`
  line `Judges and Division Courts thereof shall with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the`
  line `High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (28643)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Transfer of proceedings from Madras High Court to Andhra High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28643&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as`
  line `hereinafter provided, the High Court at Madras shall as from the prescribed day, have no jurisdiction`
  line `in respect of the State of Andhra.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Madras immediately before the prescribed day`
  line `as are certified, whether before or after that day by the Chief Justice of that High Court having regard`
  line `to the place of accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances to be proceedings which ought`
  line `to be heard and decided by the High Court of Andhra shall as soon as may be after such certification`
  line `be transferred to the High Court of Andhra.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section or in section 30,`
  line `but save as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Madras shall have and the High Court of Andhra`
  line `shall not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal`
  line `including leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where`
  line `any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order passed by the High Court at Madras`
  line `before the prescribed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after any such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Madras, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Andhra he shall order that they shall be so transferred and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court at Madras—`
  line
  line `(a) before the prescribed day, in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Andhra by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Madras retains jurisdiction by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall for all purposes have effect, not only as an order of the High Court at Madras, but also as an`
  line `order made by the High Court of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (28644)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28644&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the High Court of Andhra of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be`
  line `made on or after the prescribed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature of other`
  line `authority having power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (28645)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28645&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this section shall have effect with respect to`
  line `the period beginning on the appointed day and ending immediately before the prescribed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The jurisdiction of the High Court at Madras shall extend to the State of Andhra, and the said`
  line `High Court shall, in relation to the territories of that State, continue to have such jurisdiction as it had`
  line `immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (28646)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `High Court for the added areas of Mysore.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28646&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Mysore shall, as from the appointed day, extend to`
  line `the whole of the transferred territory, and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court at Madras shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in respect of the`
  line `transferred territory.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Madras immediately before the appointed day`
  line `as are certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court having regard to the place of accrual of the`
  line `cause of action and other circumstances to be proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the`
  line `High Court of Mysore shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the High`
  line `Court of Mysore.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter`
  line `provided, the High Court at Madras shall have, and the High Court of Mysore shall, not have,`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal including leave to`
  line `appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such`
  line `proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order passed by the High Court at Madras before the`
  line `appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after any such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Madras, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Mysore he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court at Madras—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Mysore by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Madras retains jurisdiction by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `shall for all purposes have effect, not only as an order of the High Court at Madras, but also as an`
  line `order made by the High Court of Mysore.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise or an`
  line `attorney entitled to act in the High Court at Madras and was authorised to appear or to act in any`
  line `proceedings transferred from that High Court to the High Court of Mysore under sub-section (2) or`
  line `the proviso to sub-section (3) shall, on such transfer of the proceedings, have the right to appear or to`
  line `act, as the case may be, in the High Court of Mysore in relation to those proceedings as an advocate or`
  line `an attorney entitled to practise or to act in the High Court of Mysore.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (28647)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28647&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 38 and 41—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a Court until that Court has disposed of all`
  line `issues between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the`
  line `proceedings and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal including leave to appeal`
  line `to the Supreme Court, applications for review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or`
  line `Division Court thereof, and references to an order made by a Court or a Judge shall be construed`
  line `as including references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that Court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (28648)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28648&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governor of`
  line `Madras may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State of Andhra and the Consolidated Fund of the State of Madras as he deems necessary`
  line `for a period of not more than four months beginning with the appointed day pending the sanction of`
  line `such expenditure by the Legislature of the State of Andhra or the State of Madras, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Andhra may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Andhra for any period`
  line `not extending beyond the said period of four months.`
  line
  line `(2) Rajpramukh of Mysore may also, at any time before the appointed day authorise such`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Mysore as he deems necessary for meeting the`
  line `additional expenditure in respect of the transferred territory for a period of not more than four months`
  line `beginning with the appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the`
  line State.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (28649)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Vote on account by the Madras Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28649&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Any grant made by the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Madras under sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 206 in respect of the estimated`
  line `expenditure for a part of the financial year 1953-54 and the law made by the Legislature of that State`
  line `authorising the withdrawal of moneys from the Consolidated Fund of the State for the purposes for`
  line `which the said grant has been made shall, notwithstanding that the procedure prescribed in article 203`
  line `for the voting of such grant has not been completed and the law in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `article 204 in relation to such expenditure has not been passed before the appointed day, be deemed to`
  line `be sufficient authority for all expenditure incurred before that day for the purposes for which the said`
  line `grant has been made and for the withdrawal of moneys before that day from the Consolidated Fund of`
  line `the State in relation to such expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (28650)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Authorisation under the Madras Appropriation Act to cease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28650&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day,`
  line `any Act passed by the Legislature of Madras before that day for the appropriation of any money out of`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the State to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year`
  line `1953-34 shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (28651)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of Madras State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28651&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 relating to the accounts of the State of`
  line `Madras in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of each`
  line `of the States of Andhra and Madras who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of the`
  line State.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (28652)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Apportionment of assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28652&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, the`
  line `assets and liabilities of the State of Madras immediately before the appointed day shall be apportioned`
  line `between that State and the States of Andhra and Mysore in accordance with the provisions contained`
  line `in the Seventh Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute relating to, or arising out of, such apportionment shall be referred to the President`
  line `whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (28653)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28653&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where before the appointed day the State of Madras had made any contract`
  line `in the exercise of the executive power of that State for any purposes of the State, then such contract`
  line shall—
  line
  line `(a) if such purposes are as from that day—`
  line
  line `(i) exclusively purposes of the State of Andhra, or`
  line
  line `(ii) partly purposes of the State of Andhra and partly purposes of the State of Mysore and`
  line `not purposes of the State of Madras as constituted on the appointed day,`
  line
  line `be deemed to have been made in the exercise of the executive power of the State of Andhra`
  line `instead of the State of Madras;`
  line
  line `(b) if such purposes are as from that day exclusively purposes of the State of Mysore, be`
  line `deemed to have been made in the exercise of the executive power of that State instead of the State`
  line `of Madras; and`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, continue to have effect as having been made in the exercise of the`
  line `executive power of the State of Madras;`
  line
  line `and all rights and liabilities which have accrued or may accrue under any such contract shall, to the`
  line `extent to which they would have been rights or liabilities of the State of Madras as constituted`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, be rights or liabilities of the State of Andhra, the State of`
  line `Mysore or the State of Madras, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which`
  line `have accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any Court or other tribunal in`
  line `proceedings relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such`
  line proceedings.
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the provisions relating to apportionment of liabilities`
  line `in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations contained in the Seventh schedule; and`
  line `bank balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that they partake of the nature of contractual`
  line `rights, be dealt with under the said provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (28654)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrongs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28654&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where immediately before the appointed day,`
  line `the State of Madras is subject to any liability in respect of an actionable wrong other than breach of`
  line `contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) where the cause of action arose—`
  line
  line `(i) wholly within the territories which as from that day are the territories of the State of`
  line `Andhra, or`
  line
  line `(ii) partly within the territories which as from that day are the territories of the State of`
  line `Andhra and partly within the transferred territory but not within any part of the territories`
  line `which as from that day are the territories of the State of Madras,`
  line
  line `be a liability of the State of Andhra;`
  line
  line `(b) where the cause of action arose wholly within the transferred territory, be a liability of the`
  line `State of Mysore; and`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State of Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (28655)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Liability as guarantor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28655&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `If immediately before the appointed day, the State of Madras is`
  line `liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a Co-operative Society which is registered under the`
  line `Madras Co-operative Societies Act, 1932 (6 of 1932) and whose area of operations is limited to the`
  line `whole or any part of the territories which on the appointed day become the territories of the State of`
  line `Andhra then as from that day the said liability of the State of Madras in respect of such guarantee`
  line `shall be a liability of the State of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (28656)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power of President to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28656&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Where by virtue`
  line `of any of the provisions of sections 47 to 50 or of the Seventh Schedule, any of the States of Madras,`
  line `Andhra and Mysore becomes entitled to any property or obtains any other benefits or becomes subject`
  line `to any liability, and the President is of opinion, on a reference made within a period of three years`
  line `from the appointed day, by any State concerned, that it is just and equitable that that property or those`
  line `benefits should be transferred to or shared with one or both of the other States, or a contribution`
  line `towards that liability should be made by one or both of the other States, the said property or benefits`
  line `shall be allocated in such manner, or the other State or States shall make to the State primarily subject`
  line `to the liability such contribution in respect thereof, as the President may after consultation with the`
  line `State Governments concerned, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (28657)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Certain expenditure to be charged on the Consolidated Fund of the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28657&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `All sums`
  line `payable by any of the States of Madras, Andhra and Mysore to any one of the other two States or to`
  line `the Central Government by virtue of the provisions of paragraph 12 or paragraph 17 of the Seventh`
  line `Schedule, shall be charged on the Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (28658)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28658&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part II shall not be deemed to have effect any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Madras or of Mysore shall, until`
  line `otherwise provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, continue to have the`
  line `same meaning.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (28659)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28659&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of`
  line `Andhra, Madras or Mysore of any law made before the appointed day, the appropriate Government`
  line `may, before the 1st day of April, 1954, by order make such adaptations and modifications of the law,`
  line `whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such`
  line `law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and modifications so made until altered, repealed or`
  line `amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means as respects a law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in List I of the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the Central`
  line `Government, and as respects any other law, the State Government of Andhra, Madras or Mysore, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (28660)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28660&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has`
  line `been made under section 54 of the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court,`
  line `tribunal or authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating`
  line `its application in relation to the State of Andhra, Madras or Mysore, construe the law with such`
  line `alterations not affecting the substance as may be necessary or proper to adapt it to the matter before`
  line `the Court, tribunal or authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (28661)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28661&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The Governor as`
  line `respects the State of Andhra and the Rajpramukh as respects the transferred territory may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify the authority, officer or person who as from the appointed`
  line `day shall be competent to exercise such functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as`
  line `may be mentioned in that notification and such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (28662)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Legal proceedings concerned the State of Madras.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28662&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, the State of Madras is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property,`
  line `rights or liabilities subject to apportionment between the State of Madras and the States of Andhra and`
  line `Mysore under this Act, the State which succeeds to, or acquires a share in, that property or those`
  line `rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of this Act shall be deemed to be substituted for the`
  line `State of Madras as a party to those proceedings or to be added as a party thereto, as the case may be,`
  line `and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (28663)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Provisions as to certain pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28663&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately`
  line `before the appointed day before a Court (other than the High Court), tribunal, authority or officer—`
  line
  line `(a) in any area which on that day falls within the State of Madras or the transferred territory`
  line `shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to any part of the territories which as from that day`
  line `are the territories of the State of Andhra, stand transferred to the corresponding court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer in the State of Andhra, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any area which on that day falls within the State of Madras or the State of Andhra shall,`
  line `if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to any part of the transferred territory, stand transferred to`
  line `the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in the State of Mysore.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding shall stand transferred under sub-section`
  line `(1), it shall be referred for the decision of the Chief Justice of the High Court at Madras and his`
  line `decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal, and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in relation to a State means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal authority or officer in which the proceeding would have lain if the`
  line `proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in the State as may be`
  line `determined, before the appointed day by the Governor of Madras, and after the appointed day`
  line `by the Governor or Rajpramukh of that State, to be the corresponding court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (28664)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Provisions for detention in, and power to commit to, certain jails and other institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28664&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government of Madras and the Government of Mysore shall, for a period of`
  line `five years from the appointed day, make available to the Government of Andhra the jails and other`
  line `institutions specified in Part I and Part II respectively of the Eighth Schedule for the reception and`
  line `detention of persons committed to, or ordered to be detained in, such jails or institutions by any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority in the State of Andhra.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be competent for a court, tribunal or other authority in the State of Andhra to order the`
  line `commitment to, or detention in, any of the jails and other institutions specified in the Eighth Schedule`
  line `during the period referred to in sub-section (1) of persons convicted and sentenced, or ordered to be`
  line `detained therein, by such court, tribunal or other authority notwithstanding that such jail or institution`
  line `is outside the State.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions subject to which the jails and other institutions specified in the`
  line `Eighth Schedule shall be used by the Government of Andhra for the purposes referred to in subsection`
  line `(1) shall be such as may be agreed upon between the Governments concerned by the 1st day`
  line `of January, 1954, or, if no agreement is reached by the said date, as may be fixed by order of the`
  line President.
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (28665)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28665&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The Government of Madras and the`
  line `Government of Mysore, in respect of the institutions specified in Part I and Part II, respectively, of the`
  line `Ninth Schedule shall provide for the Government and the people of the State of Andhra such facilities,`
  line `for such period and upon such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between the Governments`
  line `concerned by the 1st day of January, 1954, or, if no agreement is reached by the said date, as may be`
  line `fixed by order of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (28666)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Provisions relating to the Indian Administrative Service and the Indian Police Service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28666&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) In place of the cadres of the Indian Administrative Service and the Indian Police Service existing`
  line `in the State of Madras immediately before the appointed day, there shall, as from that day, be two`
  line `separate cadres, one for the State of Andhra and the other for the State of Madras, in respect of each`
  line `of the Services.`
  line
  line `(2) The President shall, by order, determine the strength and composition of, and the allocation of`
  line `individual officers, to the said cadres for each of the States of Andhra and Madras.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer allocated under sub-section (2) to the cadre for the State of Andhra who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is serving in connection with the affairs of the State of`
  line `Madras shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if immediately before the appointed day he is holding any post in any area which on that`
  line `day falls in the State of Andhra, be as from that day, deemed to have been duly appointed to that`
  line `post by the Government of Andhra; and`
  line
  line `(b) if immediately before the appointed day he is not holding any post in any such area, be`
  line `appointed by the Government of Andhra to a post in connection with the affairs of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (28667)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Provisions relating to the Indian Civil Service, the Indian Police, the Indian Service of Engineers and the Indian Forest Service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28667&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of the members borne on the Madras`
  line `cadre of the Services known as the Indian Civil Service, the Indian Police, the Indian Service of`
  line `Engineers and the Indian Forest Service, the President shall, by order, determine the allocation of`
  line `individual officers to the States of Andhra and Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer allocated under sub-section (1) to the State of Andhra, who immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is serving in connection with the affairs of the State of Madras shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if, immediately before the appointed day, he is holding any post in any area which on that`
  line `day falls in the State of Andhra, be deemed, as from that day, to have been duly appointed to that`
  line `post by the Government of Andhra; and`
  line
  line `(b) if, immediately before the appointed day, he is not holding any post in any such area, be`
  line `appointed by the Government of Andhra to a post in connection with the affairs of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (28668)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Provisions relating to other Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28668&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may by general order require all`
  line `persons who immediately before the appointed day are serving in connection with the affairs of the`
  line `State of Madras in the territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 or in the transferred territory`
  line `and who under the terms of their appointments or their conditions of service are not normally liable to`
  line `be transferred outside the said territories or territory in which they are serving, to serve as from the`
  line `appointed day in connection with the affairs of the State of Andhra or the State of Mysore, as the case`
  line `may be, and all allocations so made by the President shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may by special order require any person who is serving immediately before the`
  line `appointed day in connection with the affairs of the State of Madras and to whom the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) do not apply, to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Andhra.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is required to serve under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in connection`
  line `with the affairs of the State of Andhra or the State of Mysore shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if immediately before the appointed day he is holding any post in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Madras in any area which on that day falls in the State in which he is so`
  line `required to serve, be deemed as from that day to have been duly appointed to that post by the`
  line `Government of, or by other appropriate authority in the State concerned in connection with the`
  line `affairs of that State; and`
  line
  line `(b) if immediately before the appointed day he is not holding any post in any such area, be`
  line `appointed by the Government of, or by other appropriate authority in, the State concerned, to a`
  line `post in connection with the affairs of that State.`
  line
  line `(4) All persons who are required by the President under sub-section (2) to serve in connection`
  line `with the affairs of the State of Andhra shall be classified by him into the following two categories,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) officers whose allocation to the State of Andhra is final (hereinafter referred to in this`
  line `section as "allotted officers"), and`
  line
  line `(ii) officers required by the President to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of`
  line `Andhra for a limited period as provided in sub-section (5) (hereinafter referred to in this section as`
  line `"transferred officers").`
  line
  line `(5) The period for which a transferred officer may be required to serve in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Andhra shall be two years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government of Andhra may return any such officer to the State of Madras at`
  line `any time before the expiration of the said period after giving three months' notice to him and to the`
  line `Government of Madras.`
  line
  line `(6) An officer shall be classified under sub-section (4) as an allotted officer or a transferred officer`
  line `according as he is, or is not, in the opinion of the President, suitable for final allotment to the State of`
  line Andhra.
  line
  line `(7) A transferred officer shall, during the period he is required to serve in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Andhra,—`
  line
  line `(a) continue to be in the service of the State of Madras and be deemed to be on deputation to`
  line `the State of Andhra, and`
  line
  line `(b) be entitled in addition to the remuneration which he would have drawn if he had continued`
  line `during such period to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Madras, to such`
  line `allowances as the President may by general or special order determine.`
  line
  line `(8) A transferred officer shall not be dismissed, removed or reduced in rank except with the`
  line `previous concurrence of the Government of Madras, and if the Government of Madras does not`
  line `concur in any such proposal of the Government of Andhra, then the Government of Andhra shall`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5) return the officer concerned to the State of`
  line Madras.
  line
  line `(9) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (7) and (8), the conditions of service of a transferred`
  line `officer shall be the same as they would have been if he had continued to serve in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State of Madras during the period he is required to serve in connection with the affairs of`
  line `the State of Andhra.`
  line
  line `(10) The foregoing provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to any person to whom the`
  line `provisions of section 61 or section 62 apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (28669)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power of President to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28669&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The President may give such directions to the States`
  line `of Madras, Andhra and Mysore as may appear to him to be necessary for the purpose of giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of sections 61, 62 and 63 and ensuring the proper division of services among those`
  line States.
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (28670)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Report of the Madras Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28670&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `The report of the Madras Public`
  line `Service Commission as to the work done by the Commission in respect of any period prior to the`
  line `appointed day shall be presented under clause (2) of Article 323 to the Governors of Andhra and`
  line `Madras, and the Governor of Madras shall on receipt of such report cause a copy thereof together with`
  line `a memorandum explaining, as far as possible, as respects the cases, if any, where the advice of the`
  line `Commission was not accepted, the reasons for such non-acceptance to be laid before the Legislature`
  line `of the State of Madras and it shall not be necessary to cause such report or any such memorandum to`
  line `be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State of Andhra.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (28671)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Special provisions with regard to Tungabhadra Project.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28671&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act but subject to the provisions of paragraph 12 of the Seventh Schedule, all rights`
  line `and liabilities of the State of Madras in relation to Tungabhadra Project or the administration thereof`
  line `shall, on the appointed day, be the rights and liabilities of the States of Andhra and Mysore subject to`
  line `such adjustments as may be made by agreement entered into by the said States after consultation with`
  line `the President or if no such agreement is entered into within two years from the appointed day, as the`
  line `President may by order determine having due regard to the purposes of the Project, and any such`
  line `order may provide for the management of the Project jointly by the said States or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the order so made by the President may be varied by any subsequent agreement`
  line `entered into by the States of Andhra and Mysore.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement or order referred to in sub-section (1) shall, if there has been an extension or`
  line `further development of the Project after the appointed day, provide also for the rights and liabilities of`
  line `the States of Andhra and Mysore in relation to such extension or further development.`
  line
  line `(3) The rights and liabilities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall include`
  line
  line `(a) the rights to receive and to utilise water which may be available for distribution as a result`
  line `of the Project,`
  line
  line `(b) the rights to receive and to utilise the power generated as a result of the Project.`
  line
  line `(c) the rights and liabilities in respect of the administration of the Project and the construction,`
  line `maintenance and operation thereof,`
  line
  line `but shall not include the rights and liabilities under any contract entered into before the appointed`
  line `day by the Government of Madras with any person other than Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The President may from time to time give such directions as may appear to him to be`
  line `necessary generally in regard to any of the matters specified in the foregoing provisions of this section`
  line `and, in particular, for the completion of the Project and its operation and maintenance thereafter:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be issued or have effect after an agreement has been entered`
  line `into by the States of Andhra and Mysore under sub-section (1) or after an order has been made by the`
  line `President under that sub-section, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(5) In this section, the expression "Tungabhadra Project" or "the Project" means the project`
  line `agreed to between the Government of Madras and the Government of Hyderabad before the appointed`
  line `day and, so far as the State of Madras is concerned, intended for the supply and distribution of water`
  line `from the Tungabhadra river by means of high-level and low level canals to the districts of Bellary,`
  line `Anantapur, Cuddapah and Kurnool, and for the generation of electric energy, both hydro-electric and`
  line `thermal, and its transmission and distribution to the said districts and includes any extension or further`
  line `development after that day of that Project for the said purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (28672)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Allowances and privileges of the Governor of Andhra.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28672&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges of`
  line `the Governor of Andhra shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under`
  line `clause (3) of article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (28673)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28673&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (28674)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522&sectionId=28674&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00060_195330_1517807328522
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may by order do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appear`
  line `to him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
